    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Classic Horrors Revisited pg. 8</em></p><h3><span title=\"PFS Legal\">[PFS]</span> Statistics</h3><p><strong>Cost</strong> 20 gp <strong>Weight</strong> 2 lbs.</p><p><strong>Damage</strong> 1d4 (small), 1d6 (medium); <strong>Critical</strong> 18-20/x2; <strong>Range</strong> -; <strong>Type</strong> S; <strong>Special</strong> -</p><p><strong>Category</strong> Ranged; <strong>Proficiency</strong> Exotic</p><h3>Description</h3><p>Shaped and carved from quartz or stranger subterranean crystals, these circular throwing discs have jagged razor-sharp edges. When a crystal chakram strikes a foe, the weapon shatters into tiny sharp fragments; if it misses, there is a 50% chance the chakram shatters when it hits the ground or another solid object; otherwise it can be retrieved and used again. A crystal chakram is treated as ammunition for the purpose of creating magic weapons.</p>"
